This paper proposes a novel deep architecture for enhancing model discriminability and facilitating information abstraction within the receptive field. The proposed architecture is applied to image classification tasks, indicating that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of batch normalization and dropout, which are commonly used techniques in machine learning and neural networks, suggesting that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of activation functions and information abstraction, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.CL, in that order.
